1000
01:27:20,515 --> 01:27:23,075
Hadn't you better get a little rest?

1001
01:27:23,151 --> 01:27:26,848
It's a capital idea.
It may be our last.

1002
01:27:39,134 --> 01:27:40,931
They're on us.

1003
01:27:41,002 --> 01:27:43,493
Here they come. Wake up, men.
On your feet.

1004
01:27:43,572 --> 01:27:45,972
[Military bugle call]

1005
01:28:26,047 --> 01:28:28,743
Ya-hoo. We're holdin' 'em.

1006
01:28:29,784 --> 01:28:32,617
Colonel, what's that bugle call
they were playin'?

1007
01:28:32,687 --> 01:28:35,451
That's their signal for no quarter.

1008
01:28:35,523 --> 01:28:38,856
Yeah?
Well, they'll be playin' that again.

1009
01:28:49,838 --> 01:28:51,829
Here they come.

1010
01:30:30,538 --> 01:30:32,904
They've breached the north wall.

1011
01:30:32,974 --> 01:30:35,499
Let's swing the cannon.
Come on.

1012
01:31:12,180 --> 01:31:14,478
Fire in the hole!

1013
01:31:54,889 --> 01:31:57,687
Give 'em what for, Davy.

1014
01:32:15,944 --> 01:32:19,141
# Storybooks tell
They was all cut low

1015
01:32:19,214 --> 01:32:22,911
# But the truth of it is
This just ain't so

1016
01:32:22,984 --> 01:32:26,476
# Their spirits'll live
And their legends grow

1017
01:32:26,554 --> 01:32:30,046
# As long as we remember
The Alamo

1018
01:32:30,124 --> 01:32:33,457
# Davy, Davy Crockett

1019
